Design a modern, clean, sport-inspired website for a tchoukball club called “Tchouk'Leu” located in Saint-Leu, on Reunion Island.

The visual identity must combine sport energy + tropical island atmosphere.

The club logo includes a shield, a tchoukball frame, and a paille-en-queue bird (white tropical bird emblematic of Reunion Island).

The design must highlight:
	•	the lagoon and beach environment of Saint-Leu
	•	the light blue ocean colors
	•	the local identity of Reunion Island
	•	the paille-en-queue bird as a graphic element

The style should feel modern, airy, sporty, and tropical.

⸻

Color palette

Primary colors inspired by the logo and lagoon:

Primary lagoon blue
#BFE6FF

Light sky blue
#DDF4FF

Ocean accent blue
#4C93C3

White
#FFFFFF

Dark text
#1F2A37

The interface should stay very light and breathable with lots of white space.

⸻

Typography

Use a modern sans-serif font suitable for sports websites.

Example style:
	•	bold geometric titles
	•	clean readable body text

Headings should feel strong and dynamic, like a sports brand.

⸻

Homepage structure

1 — Fullscreen Hero Section

The homepage starts with a full-screen photograph of Saint-Leu beach and lagoon.

Important:
When the page loads, only the photo is visible.
There is no header initially.

Centered on the image:

Club logo

Title:
Tchouk'Leu

Subtitle:
Tchoukball Club – Saint-Leu, Réunion

Optional tagline:
“Between lagoon, light and team spirit”

Primary button:
Discover the club

Secondary button:
Join us

Add a subtle scroll indicator at the bottom.

The hero image should evoke:
	•	lagoon
	•	beach
	•	horizon
	•	tropical light

Overlay with a very subtle light blue gradient to keep text readable.

⸻

2 — Sticky Header (appears on scroll)

The header becomes visible after scrolling.

Style:
	•	semi-transparent white background
	•	slight blur effect
	•	smooth fade-in animation

Left:
club logo

Right navigation:

Home
The Club
Training
Gallery
Contact

Hover color:
lagoon blue.

